msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:0.3"
msgid "Pācittiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on confession (_pācittiya_)"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:0.4"
msgid "Ovādavagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 22"

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:0.5"
msgid "22. Atthaṅgatasikkhāpada"
msgstr "The training rule on gone down"

#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-vp-pli4.54, pts-cs-bu-pc22.1, pts-vp-en.2.273, ms2V_517
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena therā bhikkhū bhikkhuniyo ovadanti pariyāyena."
msgstr "At that time the senior monks were instructing the nuns in turn,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:1.3"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmato cūḷapanthakassa pariyāyo hoti bhikkhuniyo ovadituṃ."
msgstr "and on one occasion it was the turn of Venerable Cūḷapanthaka."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:1.4"
msgid "Bhikkhuniyo evamāhaṃsu—"
msgstr "The nuns said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:1.5"
msgid "“na dāni ajja ovādo iddho bhavissati, taññeva dāni udānaṃ ayyo cūḷapanthako punappunaṃ bhaṇissatī”ti."
msgstr "“Today the instruction won’t be effective, since Venerable Cūḷapanthaka will just be repeating the same utterance over and over.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:1.6"
msgid "Atha kho tā bhikkhuniyo yenāyasmā cūḷapanthako tenupasaṅkamiṃsu;"
msgstr "Soon afterwards those nuns went to Cūḷapanthaka,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:1.7"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ cūḷapanthakaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu."
msgstr "bowed down to him, and sat down to one side."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:1.8"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho tā bhikkhuniyo āyasmā cūḷapanthako etadavoca—"
msgstr "Cūḷapanthaka then said to them,"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:1.9"
msgid "“samaggāttha, bhaginiyo”ti?"
msgstr "“Are you all present, Sisters?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:1.10"
msgid "“Samaggāmhāyyā”ti."
msgstr "“We’re all present, Venerable.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:1.11"
msgid "“Vattanti, bhaginiyo, aṭṭha garudhammā”ti?"
msgstr "“Are you keeping the eight rules to be respected?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:1.12"
msgid "“Vattantāyyā”ti."
msgstr "“We are.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:1.13"
msgid "“Eso, bhaginiyo, ovādo”ti niyyādetvā imaṃ udānaṃ punappunaṃ abhāsi—"
msgstr "After saying, “This is the instruction,” he spoke the same utterance again and again:"

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc2, ms2V_518
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:1.14"
msgid "“Adhicetaso appamajjato,"
msgstr "“For the heedful one possessed of the higher mind,"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:1.15"
msgid "Munino monapathesu sikkhato;"
msgstr "For the sage training on the path to sagacity,"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:1.16"
msgid "Sokā na bhavanti tādino,"
msgstr "There are no sorrows for such a one,"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:1.17"
msgid "Upasantassa sadā satīmato”ti."
msgstr "The peaceful one, who is always mindful.”"

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc3, pts-vp-en.2.274, ms2V_519
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:1.18"
msgid "Bhikkhuniyo evamāhaṃsu—"
msgstr "And the nuns said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:1.19"
msgid "“nanu avocumhā—na dāni ajja ovādo iddho bhavissati, taññeva dāni udānaṃ ayyo cūḷapanthako punappunaṃ bhaṇissatī”ti."
msgstr "“Didn’t we say that the instruction wouldn’t be effective, that Venerable Cūḷapanthaka would just be repeating the same utterance over and over?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:1.20"
msgid "Assosi kho āyasmā cūḷapanthako tāsaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ imaṃ kathāsallāpaṃ."
msgstr "But Cūḷapanthaka overheard that conversation between the nuns."

#. VAR: tañceva → taññeva (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:1.21"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā cūḷapanthako vehāsaṃ abbhuggantvā ākāse antalikkhe caṅkamatipi tiṭṭhatipi nisīdatipi seyyampi kappeti dhūmāyatipi pajjalatipi antaradhāyatipi, tañceva udānaṃ bhaṇati aññañca bahuṃ buddhavacanaṃ."
msgstr "He then rose up into the air, walked back and forth in space, and he stood, sat down, and lay down there. He emitted smoke and fire, and he disappeared, all the while speaking the same utterance and many other sayings by the Buddha."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:1.22"
msgid "Bhikkhuniyo evamāhaṃsu—"
msgstr "And the nuns said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:1.23"
msgid "“acchariyaṃ vata bho, abbhutaṃ vata bho."
msgstr "“It’s astonishing and amazing!"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:1.24"
msgid "Na vata no ito pubbe ovādo evaṃ iddho bhūtapubbo yathā ayyassa cūḷapanthakassā”ti."
msgstr "No previous instruction has been as effective as this one from Venerable Cūḷapanthaka!”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:1.25"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā cūḷapanthako tā bhikkhuniyo yāva samandhakārā ovaditvā uyyojesi—"
msgstr "And Cūḷapanthaka kept on instructing those nuns until the dark of night, and then dismissed them, saying,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:1.26"
msgid "“gacchatha, bhaginiyo”ti."
msgstr "“Go, Sisters.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4, ms2V_520
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:1.27"
msgid "Atha kho tā bhikkhuniyo nagaradvāre thakite bahinagare vasitvā kālasseva nagaraṃ pavisanti."
msgstr "But because the gates to the town were closed, those nuns stayed the night outside and entered in the morning."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:1.28"
msgid "Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "People complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:1.29"
msgid "“abrahmacāriniyo imā bhikkhuniyo;"
msgstr "“These nuns aren’t celibate."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:1.30"
msgid "ārāme bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ vasitvā idāni nagaraṃ pavisantī”ti."
msgstr "They spend the night in the monastery with the monks and only now do they enter the town.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5, pts-vp-pli4.55, ms2V_521
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:1.31"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ."
msgstr "The monks heard the complaints of those people,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:1.32"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "and the monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:1.33"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized Cūḷapanthaka,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:1.34"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma āyasmā cūḷapanthako atthaṅgate sūriye bhikkhuniyo ovadissatī”ti … pe …"
msgstr "“How can Venerable Cūḷapanthaka instruct the nuns after the sun has set?”…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:1.35"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, cūḷapanthaka, atthaṅgate sūriye bhikkhuniyo ovadasī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, Cūḷapanthaka, that you did this?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:1.36"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:1.37"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked him, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:1.38"
msgid "kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, cūḷapanthaka, atthaṅgate sūriye bhikkhuniyo ovadissasi."
msgstr "Cūḷapanthaka, how can you instruct the nuns after the sun has set?"

#. REF: pts-vp-en.2.275
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:1.39"
msgid "Netaṃ, cūḷapanthaka, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without  it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:1.40"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:1.40a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="rule">
#. VAR: sūriye → suriye (s1-3, pts1)
#. VAR: Sammatopi ce → sammato ce pi (pts1)
#. REF: sc6, ms2V_522,  
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:1.41"
msgid "“Sammatopi ce bhikkhu atthaṅgate sūriye bhikkhuniyo ovadeyya, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "‘Even if he has been agreed upon, if a monk instructs the nuns after sunset, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:2.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc7, pts-cs-bu-pc21.2.1, ms2V_523
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:2.1.1"
msgid "Sammato nāma"
msgstr "Who has been agreed upon:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:2.1.2"
msgid "ñatticatutthena kammena sammato."
msgstr "who has been agreed upon through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc8, ms2V_524
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:2.1.3"
msgid "Atthaṅgate sūriyeti"
msgstr "After sunset:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:2.1.4"
msgid "oggate sūriye."
msgstr "after the sun has gone down."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc9, ms2V_525
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:2.1.5"
msgid "Bhikkhunī nāma"
msgstr "The nuns:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:2.1.6"
msgid "ubhatosaṃghe upasampannā."
msgstr "they have been given the full ordination by both Orders."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc10, ms2V_526
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:2.1.7"
msgid "Ovadeyyāti"
msgstr "Instructs:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:2.1.8"
msgid "aṭṭhahi vā garudhammehi aññena vā dhammena ovadati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "if he instructs in the eight rules to be respected or he gives any other teaching, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:2.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc11, pts-cs-bu-pc22.2.2, ms2V_527
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:2.2.1"
msgid "Atthaṅgate atthaṅgatasaññī ovadati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If the sun has set, and he perceives that it has, and he instructs the nuns, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:2.2.2"
msgid "Atthaṅgate vematiko ovadati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If the sun has set, but he is unsure if it has, and he instructs the nuns, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:2.2.3"
msgid "Atthaṅgate anatthaṅgatasaññī ovadati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If the sun has set, but he perceives that it has not, and he instructs the nuns, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12, ms2V_528
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:2.2.4"
msgid "Ekatoupasampannāya ovadati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he instructs a nun who is fully ordained only on one side, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:2.2.5"
msgid "Anatthaṅgate atthaṅgatasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If the sun has not set, but he perceives that it has, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:2.2.6"
msgid "Anatthaṅgate vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If the sun has not set, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:2.2.7"
msgid "Anatthaṅgate anatthaṅgatasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr "If the sun has not set, and he perceives that it has not, there is no offense."

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:2.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc13, pts-cs-bu-pc22.2.3, ms2V_529
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:2.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:2.3.2"
msgid "uddesaṃ dento, paripucchaṃ dento,"
msgstr "if he gives a summary;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:2.3.3"
msgid "“osārehi ayyā”ti vuccamāno,"
msgstr "if he questions them;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:2.3.4"
msgid "osāreti,"
msgstr "if he recites when asked to do so;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:2.3.5"
msgid "pañhaṃ pucchati,"
msgstr "if he asks a question;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:2.3.6"
msgid "pañhaṃ puṭṭho katheti,"
msgstr "if he replies when asked a question;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:2.3.7"
msgid "aññassatthāya bhaṇantaṃ bhikkhuniyo suṇanti,"
msgstr "if he is speaking for the benefit of someone else and the nuns listen in;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:2.3.8"
msgid "sikkhamānāya,"
msgstr "if it is to a trainee nun;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:2.3.9"
msgid "sāmaṇeriyā,"
msgstr "if it is to a novice nun;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:2.3.10"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:2.3.11"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. HTML: </p><hr><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc14, ms2V_530
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc22:2.3.12"
msgid "Atthaṅgatasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dutiyaṃ."
msgstr "The second rule, the training rule on gone down, is finished."
